<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Read this my holier than thou freind</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Angus[CC]">Angus[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:24 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Read this my holier than thou freind<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=748" TARGET=_self>Now that I've read it, I just don't agree..</A> (Geiger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I'm a 27 year old Banker, not a "snot-nosed Jr high jerk". And once again your whole arguement is invalidated

<BR>by your blatant ignorance of the real PvP community. I have never, and will never give any credit or consideration
<BR>to anyone that cannot stop themselves from stereotyping every PvP+ person into the so called "L33t" catagory.
<P>You clearly have no place posting on this board at all. You have no helpful feedback to give on the PvP system in EQ
<BR>so please put these comments elsewhere. Geiger was kind to even respond to that drivel you call a post. This board is
<BR>for bettering the PvP enviorment in EQ for those enclined to PvP combat. I had to put up with flamers like you on the beta board
<BR>and was prohibited from responding to the endless flames by folks who hate PvP. Please take this else where, we don't need it here.
<P>Thanks and have a nice day =P
<P>yours,
<P>Angus The Grim[CC]
<P>&gt; The first and biggest mistake you made was to stereotype PvP to
<BR>&gt; what you saw in UO.
<P>&gt; The second thing you did was try to segregate PvP from Roleplay.
<BR>&gt; Roleplay in the truest form of the word has as much to do with
<BR>&gt; PvP as it does with PvE. Let think for a second. Are there any
<BR>&gt; PvE People apposed to killing bandits or brigands? It was
<BR>&gt; actually a quite popular way to obtain chrysknives at one time.
<BR>&gt; What is the difference as far as role play is concered from
<BR>&gt; Killing a bandit for money or items or just for storyline or
<BR>&gt; actually killing a Rogue controlled by another player for money
<BR>&gt; or items or storyline? THe only difference is that you'll have
<BR>&gt; to deal with the human side rather than a predictable NPC. That
<BR>&gt; has absolutely nothing (IMO) to do with Roleplaying, the turnoff
<BR>&gt; comes at the hands of those who would dance the Cha Cha Cha on
<BR>&gt; your corpse and Taunt you after they killed you with
<BR>&gt; "Owned" and "Thats right Biatch!". Yes there
<BR>&gt; exists a turnoff to PvP (can come from the human factor), but
<BR>&gt; that is hardly a complete or accurate representation what PvP
<BR>&gt; is, rather just a small part of it that is undesirable. Its our
<BR>&gt; mission here to REDEFINE PvP UNIQUELY for EQ. It should
<BR>&gt; definitely be part of the community.
<P>&gt; Geiger
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
